# .projects.local.md — Private Projects Registry

Copy this file to `.projects.local.md` in your repo root. It is gitignored — your project names and paths never leak into the upstream repo.

When this file exists, AI agents read it alongside `AGENTS.md` as the authoritative project registry for this workspace.

---

## Projects Registry (Private)

| Project | Collection | Notes Path |
|---------|-----------|------------|
| my-app | my-app | `projects/my-app/` |
| my-client | my-client | `projects/my-client/` |
| side-project | side-project | `projects/side-project/` |

**Repositories:** Each project's associated repos are listed in `projects/<name>/repos.json`. The panel reads this file to show git status per repo.

## Project-Specific Rules

Add any project-specific agent behavior overrides here, for example:

### my-client
- Uses yarn (not npm or pnpm)
- Never commit CLAUDE.md (gitignored in that repo)
